            "id": "7bd2341c328749a0942c9",
            "questionText": "A biomedical researcher uses a micrometer screw gauge to measure the diameter of a microscopic fiber. The gauge exhibits a zero error of $!$+0.0002\\,mm$!$, and the observed reading is $!$0.0235\\,mm$!$. Calculate the actual diameter of the fiber in $!$nm$!$, expressing your answer in standard notation with the correct number of significant figures.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "168819b106f14254a35af",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by correcting the observed reading by removing the zero error. Identify the formula that correctly represents the correction needed when a measuring instrument shows a zero error.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "9a4da118-2c7f-416d-9990-5c7e8ca6e378"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Corrected reading} = \\text{Observed reading} + \\text{Zero error}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Corrected reading} = \\text{Observed reading} - \\text{Zero error}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Corrected reading} = \\text{Observed reading} \\times \\text{Zero error}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "ea77fa0e7176430a95b18",
                    "stepText": "Great, now use the selected formula to calculate the corrected reading by subtracting the zero error from the observed reading.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.0233"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "mm",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "9a4da118-2c7f-416d-9990-5c7e8ca6e378"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "985de91701114acb8e600",
                    "stepText": "Next, we need to convert the corrected reading from millimetres to nanometres. Choose the correct conversion factor for converting $!$mm$!$ to $!$nm$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "97df9a78-627f-40ae-8aef-c68ba9dd9ec7"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$1\\,mm = 10^3\\,nm$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$1\\,mm = 10^6\\,nm$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$1\\,mm = 10^9\\,nm$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "556777ead6e34111ab3b4",
                    "stepText": "Now, calculate the actual diameter in nanometres by applying the conversion factor you chose to the corrected reading.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
